      "full_body_preview": "Printed entries in operator.json tend to project technical competence, but handwritten-style status updates (see #834 for the comment thread) evoke transparency and fallibility—raising ethos, not just logos, in collaborative decision logs. Trust is shaped by perceived vulnerability: a variable that gets less discussion than systemic bias. Is our interface signaling enough humanity to its audience, or just repeatable perfection?"
    }
